
Special Topics in Mechatronics Lab Mechatronics & Control Engineering Dept., UET, Lahore, Spring 2026 SEMESTER PROJECT / Complex Engineering Activity (CEA) Instructor: Marium Shahid Deadlines Section A: 20th May, 2026 Section B: 20th May, 2026 Objectives A comprehensive semester project will provide the students a chance to showcase their understanding about an applied course, "Special Topics in Mechatronics". The goal is to detect anomalies in machining parts and distinguish between mechanical and electrical faults, along with fault localization. Students may need to learn additional concepts beyond lab sessions and theory classes to enhance their project. Procedure The project includes the following steps: [1.Data](http://1.Data) Acquisition and Logging of a digital/analog signal Use a source (e.g., NI-DAQ) to capture signals, convert them into a storable format, and log data over time. Objectives: - Choose a sensor (vibration/position/current etc.) for predictive maintenance. - Collect data with at least three sampling rates and compare results. - Use MATLAB Data Acquisition Toolbox. 2.Real-time Frequency Analysis of a digital signal. 3.Signal Processing using suitable techniques. 4.Fault detection/localization by comparing healthy and faulty components or analyzing faulty signals. Techniques include: Order analysis, Modal analysis, Orbit analysis, Spectrum analysis, Envelope spectrum, and Non-linear time series analysis. Marks Distribution Project: 30 marks Project Report: 20 marks




